[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-<\u001b[m\u000f Scroll Left\u001b[67;2H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fX\u001b[m\u000f Exit  \u001b[67;18H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^R\u001b[m\u000f Read File     \u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^\\\u001b[m\u000f Replace       \u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^U\u001b[m\u000f Paste \u001b[67;69H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^J\u001b[m\u000f Justify\u001b[86G\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^/\u001b[m\u000f Go To Line    \u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-E\u001b[m\u000f Redo\u001b[67;120H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-6\u001b[m\u000f Copy\u001b[67;137H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^B\u001b[m\u000f Where Was     \u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM-F\u001b[m\u000f Next\u001b[67;171H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f▸\u001b[m\u000f Forward\u001b[67;188H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^▸\u001b[m\u000f Next Word     \u001b[0;10;7m\u000f^E\u001b[m\u000f End\u001b[67;222H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000fM->\u001b[m\u000f Scroll Right"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\u001b[2duser_dir =\u001b[K\r\u001b[3d\u001b[K\u001b[4d; Directory in which the loadable extensions (modules) reside.\u001b[5;3Hhttps://php.net/extension-dir\u001b[K\r\u001b[6dextension_dir = \"/usr/lib/php-legacy/modules/\"\u001b[7;3HOn windows:\u001b[K\r\u001b[8d;extension_dir = \"ext\"\u001b[K\r\u001b[9d\u001b[K\u001b[10d; Directory where the temporary files should be placed.\r\u001b[11d; Defaults to the system default (see sys_get_temp_dir)\r\u001b[12d;sys_temp_dir = \"/tmp\"\u001b[K\r\u001b[13d\u001b[K\u001b[14d; Whether or not to enable the dl() function.  The dl() function does NOT work\u001b[15;3Hproperly in multithreaded servers, such as IIS or Zeus, and is automatically\u001b[16;3Hdisabled on them.\u001b[K\u001b[17d\benable-dl\u001b[K\r\u001b[18denable_dl = Off\u001b[K\u001b[20;3Hcgi.force_redirect is necessary to provide security running PHP as a CGI under\u001b[21;3Hmost web servers.  Left undefined, PHP turns this on by default.  You can\u001b[22;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "turn it off here AT YOUR OWN RISK\u001b[K\u001b[23;3H**You CAN safely turn this off for IIS, in fact, you MUST.**\u001b[K\u001b[24;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.force-redirect\u001b[K\r\u001b[25d;cgi.force_redirect = 1\u001b[K\r\u001b[26d\u001b[K\u001b[27d;"]
[0.000, "o", " if cgi.nph is enabled it will force cgi to always sent Status: 200 with\r\u001b[28d; every request. PHP's default behavior is to disable this feature.\r\u001b[29d;cgi.nph = 1\u001b[K\r\u001b[30d\u001b[K\u001b[31;4Hf cgi.force_redirect is turned on, and you are not running under Apache or Netscape\u001b[32;3H(iPlanet) web servers, you MAY need to set an environment variable name that PHP\r\u001b[33d"]
[0.000, "o", "; will look for to know it is OK to continue \u001b[30m\u001b[43mexecution\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000f.  Setting this variable MAY\r\u001b[34d; cause security issues, KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING FIRST.\u001b[35;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "https://php.net/cgi.redirect-status-env\u001b[K\r\u001b[36d;cgi.redirect_status_env =\u001b[K\r\u001b[37d\u001b[K\u001b[38d"]
[0.000, "o", "; cgi.fix_pathinfo provides *real* PATH_INFO/PATH_TRANSLATED support for CGI.  PHP's\u001b[39;3Hprevious behaviour was to set PATH_TRANSLATED to SCRIPT_FILENAME, and to not grok\u001b[40;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "what PATH_INFO is.  For more information on PATH_INFO, see the cgi specs.  Setting\r\u001b[41d; this to 1 will cause PHP CGI to fix its paths to conform to the spec.  A setting\r\u001b[42d; of zero causes PHP to behave as before.  Default is 1.  You should fix your scripts\u001b[43;3Hto use SCRIPT_FILENAME rather than PATH_TRANSLATED.\u001b[K\u001b[44;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.fix-pathinfo\u001b[K\r\u001b[45d;cgi.fix_pathinfo=1\r\u001b[46d\u001b[K\u001b[47d; if cgi.discard_path is enabled,"]
[0.000, "o", " the PHP CGI binary can safely be placed outside\r\u001b[48d; of the web tree and people will not be able to circumvent .htaccess security.\r\u001b[49d"]
[0.000, "o", ";cgi.discard_path=1\r\u001b[50d\u001b[K\u001b[51d; "]
[0.001, "o", "FastCGI under IIS supports the ability to impersonate\r\u001b[52d; security tokens of the calling client.  This allows IIS to define the\r\u001b[53d"]
[0.000, "o", "; security context that the request runs under.  mod_fastcgi under Apache\u001b[54;3Hdoes not currently support this feature (03/17/2002)\u001b[55;3HSet to 1 if running under IIS.  Default is zero.\u001b[56;19H"]
[0.000, "o", "fastcgi.impersonate\r\u001b[57d;fastcgi.impersonate = 1\u001b[59;3HDisable logging through FastCGI connection. PHP's default behavior is to enable\u001b[60;3Hthis feature"]
