[0.001, "o", "\r\u001b[2d; maintain an idle persistent connection. Using -1 means idle\r\u001b[3d; persistent connections will be maintained forever.\u001b[4;3Hhttps://php.net/oci8.persistent-timeout\u001b[K\r\u001b[5d;oci8.persistent_timeout = -1\u001b[K\r\u001b[6d\u001b[K\u001b[7d; Connection: The number of seconds that must pass before issuing a\r\u001b[8d; ping during oci_pconnect() to check the connection validity. When\r\u001b[9d; set to 0, each oci_pconnect() will cause a ping. Using -1 disables\u001b[10;3Hpings completely.\u001b[K\u001b[11;3Hhttps://php.net/oci8.ping-interval\u001b[K\r\u001b[12d;oci8.ping_interval = 60\u001b[14;3HConnection: Set this to a user chosen connection class to be used\u001b[K\u001b[15;3Hfor all pooled server requests with Oracle Database Resident\u001b[K\u001b[16;3HConnection Pooling (DRCP).  To use DRCP, this value should be set to\u001b[17;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "the same string for all web servers running the same application,\r\u001b[18d; the database pool must be configured, and the connection string must\r\u001b[19d; specify to use a pooled server.\r\u001b[20d;oci8.connection_class =\u001b[K\r\u001b[21d"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[22d; High Availability: Using On lets PHP receive Fast Application\u001b[23;3HNotification (FAN) events generated when a database node fails. The\u001b[24;3Hdatabase must also be configured to post FAN events.\r\u001b[25d;oci8.events = Off\u001b[K\u001b[27;3HTuning: This option enables statement caching, and specifies how\u001b[K\u001b[28;3Hmany statements to cache. Using 0 disables statement caching"]
