[0.001, "o", "\r\u001b[3d; This option forces PHP to fetch and use a cookie for storing and maintaining\u001b[4;3Hthe session id. We encourage this operation as it's very helpful in combating\r\u001b[5d; session hijacking when not specifying and managing your own session id. It is\r\u001b[6d; not the be-all and end-all of session hijacking defense, but it's a good start.\u001b[7;3Hhttps://php.net/session.use-only-cookies\r\u001b[8dsession.use_only_cookies = 1\u001b[K\r\u001b[9d\u001b[K\u001b[10d; Name of the session (used as cookie name).\u001b[11;3Hhttps://php.net/session.name\u001b[K\r\u001b[12dsession.name = PHPSESSID\r\u001b[13d\u001b[K\u001b[14d; Initialize session on request startup.\r\u001b[15d; https://php.net/session.auto-start\r\u001b[16dsession.auto_start = 0\u001b[K\r\u001b[17d\u001b[K\u001b[18d"]
[0.000, "o", "; Lifetime in seconds of cookie or, if 0, until browser is restarted.\r\u001b[19d; https://php.net/session.cookie-lifetime\r\u001b[20dsession.cookie_lifetime = 0\u001b[K\r\u001b[21d\u001b[K\u001b[22d"]
[0.000, "o", "; The path for which the cookie is valid.\r\u001b[23d; https://php.net/session.cookie-path\r\u001b[24dsession.cookie_path = /\r\u001b[25d\u001b[K\u001b[26d"]
[0.000, "o", "; The domain for which the cookie is valid.\u001b[27;3Hhttps://php.net/session.cookie-domain\u001b[K\r\u001b[28dsession.cookie_domain =\u001b[K\r\u001b[29d\u001b[K\u001b[30d"]
[0.000, "o", "; Whether or not to add the httpOnly flag to the cookie, which makes it\u001b[31;3Hinaccessible to browser scripting languages such as JavaScript.\u001b[K\u001b[32;19Hsession.cookie-httponly\r\u001b[33d"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[30m\u001b[43msession.cookie_httponly\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000f =\u001b[35;3HAdd SameSite attribute to cookie to help mitigate Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF/XSRF)\u001b[36;3HCurrent valid values are \"Strict\", \"Lax\" or \"None\". When using \"None\",\u001b[37;3Hmake sure to include the quotes, as `none` is interpreted like `false` in ini files.\r\u001b[38d; https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-west-first-party-cookies-07\r\u001b[39dsession.cookie_samesite =\r\u001b[40d\u001b[K\u001b[41d; Handler used to serialize data. php is the standard serializer of PHP.\r\u001b[42d;"]
[0.001, "o", " https://php.net/session.serialize-handler\r\u001b[43dsession.serialize_handler = php\r\u001b[44d\u001b[K\u001b[45d; "]
[0.000, "o", "Defines the probability that the 'garbage collection' process is started on every\r\u001b[46d; session initialization. The probability is calculated by using gc_probability/gc_divisor,\r\u001b[47d"]
[0.000, "o", "; e.g. 1/100 means there is a 1% chance that the GC process starts on each request.\u001b[48;3HDefault Value: 1\u001b[K\u001b[49;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "Development Value: 1\u001b[K\u001b[50;3HProduction Value: 1\u001b[K\u001b[51;3Hhttps://php.net/session.gc-probability\u001b[K\r\u001b[52d"]
[0.000, "o", "session.gc_probability = 1\u001b[K\r\u001b[53d\u001b[K\u001b[54d;"]
[0.000, "o", " Defines the probability that the 'garbage collection' process is started on every\r\u001b[55d; session initialization. The probability is calculated by using gc_probability/gc_divisor,\r\u001b[56d;"]
[0.000, "o", " e.g. 1/100 means there is a 1% chance that the GC process starts on each request.\u001b[57;3HFor high volume production servers, using a value of 1000 is a more efficient approach.\r\u001b[58d;"]
[0.000, "o", " Default Value: 100\u001b[K\r\u001b[59d; Development Value: 1000\u001b[60;3HProduction Value: 1000\u001b[K\u001b[61;3Hhttps://php.net/session.gc-divisor\r\u001b[62d"]
[0.000, "o", "session.gc_divisor = 1000\r\u001b[63d\u001b[K\u001b[64d; "]
[0.000, "o", "After this number of seconds, stored data will be seen as 'garbage' and\r\u001b[33d"]
